Right, it's okay on keto since it doesn't raise bloodsugar but a quick google search says technically it breaks a fast, although some list it as allowed. I think often the benefit of the fasting is to keep insulin low to be able to draw fat from storage and at least broth doesn't interfere with that. There is also the alternate day fasting, where you eat one day and fast the next by staying below 500 kcal (not a true fast)... so I think there are so many variations you can do to find your personal best diet even if not 100%.

we just had our 3rd birthday last monday. the xxl blocks he got are no good, too overwhelming... I thought those would be so well received since he likes playing with normal blocks lately... but the radio flyer wagon was a hit, too dangerous inside but great outside to help garden etc. the lego duplo sets were not well received, he only throws them around instead of building with them. The play kitchen from christmas gets some attention, not much and the little drumsets rather none. in general the baby slide is still hot and stuffed animals are the most fav things that never get old. I will soon invest, I say invest since they are god awful expensive in small .. animals, the high quality ones you buy singly idk, there a brand name since he is all over those in therapy. on the side note, cocomelon is the absolute fav and really only tv he watches (on youtube), such a good match he ate, well not ate but nibbled and spit out a piece of carrot and apple the last days for the first time!!!
